comments: Wiseman (DET) reaches for the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Porzingis' (WAS) head while the latter secures the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
McGruder (DET) momentarily rests a forearm on Beal's (WAS) upper right leg as he elevates and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Porzingis (WAS) gets to the height of the ball and deflects it away from Wiseman (DET) during the rebound.
Porzingis (WAS) releases the ball from his hand prior to stepping OOB.
Kuzma (WAS) momentarily brings a hand toward Ivey's (DET) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Porzingis (WAS) is slightly turning his backside and marginal contact occurs with Livers (DET) as he moves over the pick.
Porzingis (WAS) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Ivey (DET), which affects his driving shot attempt.
Ivey (DET) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard Beal (WAS).
Livers (DET) moves alongside Beal's (WAS) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs with Beal's off-arm during the driving shot attempt.
Livers (DET) maintains his right hand on the side of the ball during his dribble.
Kuzma (WAS) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it prior to incidental arm contact occurring thereafter with Livers (DET) during the driving shot attempt.
McGruder (DET) slides laterally alongside Beal's (WAS) path and marginal body contact occurs as the two come together during the driving shot attempt.
Joseph (DET) swipes down in Beal's (WAS) path and avoids making contact with Beal during the driving shot attempt.
Gafford (WAS) and Livers (DET) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
